From Ed Baranoski Subject Re How to speed up games marginally realistic In article David Madden writes Another pair of suggestions Remove the Balk It is the runners responsibility to stay safe no matter what the pitcher If a pitcher throws to an occupied base more than X time X to without successfully picking off the runner the runner advances a base as if This last suggestion will probably increase the number of stolen bases Suppose the pitcher uses up N of his N pick off The runner can probably stretch his lead off the base given that there will be extra pressure on the pitcher to get it right this Would this suggestion apply to pick off attempts per pitch per batter or per base runner on the same base Edward Baranoski MIT Lincoln Laboratory It's got to be the going J PO Box not the getting there that's good Lexington MA Harry Chapin from Greyhound